ed software cannot be installed, used or run for commercial operations. If necessary, written authorization and permission from Essence must be obtained in advance.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>3.5. XXXX&nbsp;may change, upgrade or transfer the licensed software and its related functions from time to time, and may add new functions or services to the licensed software system. If there is no independent agreement for the above new functions and services, you can still obtain authorization for the corresponding functions and services, and this Agreement shall apply.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>3.6. You are responsible for the accuracy, reliability, completeness and legality of the input data as well as the legality of the way you obtain the data, and you should regularly back up data, information, etc. You bear all risks for damage or loss of such data.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>3.7. You should keep your account number and password properly. If you find that there is a security risk in your account (including but not limited to user password leakage), you should notify XXXX&nbsp;in time, and XXXX&nbsp;will assist you in taking relevant measures. Otherwise, you are responsible for all actions under your account and you bear all responsibilities.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">&nbsp;</p><p><br></p>', NULL, 'en', '1', 1, 0, 1, '2022-04-29 15:07:16', '2024-01-22 10:23:00', NULL);
